"title": "7748: overseers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7748",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In the OT a variety of supervisory roles are mentioned. In the NT “overseers” (traditionally translated “bishops”) describes the role of local church leaders.</p>\n<h2>Overseers in the OT</h2>\n<h3>In secular life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:6\">EXO 5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:5-Ruth2:6\">RUT 2:5–2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:16\">1KI 5:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:2\">2CH 2:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:5\">NEH 3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:6-Prov6:7\">PRO 6:6–6:7</a></p>\n<h3>In religious life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:22\">NUM 8:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:2\">1CH 25:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:18\">2CH 23:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:9\">EZR 3:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh11:11\">NEH 11:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:1\">JER 20:1</a></p>\n<h2>Overseers in the NT</h2>\n<h3>In secular life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:8\">MAT 20:8</a></p>\n<h3>In the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:1\">PHP 1:1</a></strong> <em>A title for local church leaders.</em></p>\n<h3>The role of local church ``elders''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a></strong> <em>Here, as elsewhere in the NT, “elders” and “overseers” are virtually synonymous.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1-1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:1–5:4</a></p>\n<h3>Their qualifications</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1-1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:1–3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:7\">TIT 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>A title of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:25\">1PE 2:25</a></strong></p>",
